# Internal Links Loop (Strict)

Follow this loop exactly for internal-link insertion tasks.

1. Create `temp_internal_links_checklist.txt` with one line per article and no extra text:
   - Format: `- [ ] <article-path>`
2. Pick the first unchecked article.
3. Identify valid internal destinations from pages/articles/tags/categories for this article.
4. Insert internal links only inside paragraph hypertext (no titles or other formatting containers).
5. Ensure the article has at least 10 internal links.
6. Ensure all hyperlink text values are unique within that article.
7. Ensure every link points to a different internal path within that article.
8. Ensure no button-based links are counted.
9. Run local dev server and review the live article page output.
10. Mark the article as done in checklist:
   - Format: `- [x] <article-path>`
11. Continue until no unchecked lines remain.

Hard requirements:
- At least 10 internal links per article.
- Links can point only to internal pages/articles/tags/categories.
- All links must use paragraph hypertext only.
- No title links, heading links, or non-paragraph formatting links.
- Buttons do not count as internal-link quota entries.
- Hyperlink text must be unique per article.
- Each link target path must be unique per article.
- Preserve content schema fields and required frontmatter keys.
- Add explicit error logging for each loop step.
- Never modify unrelated files or unrelated schema fields.
